# Refactor Sprint / Kuperman Advisors - Project Rules

## Project Overview

This is a dual-domain Next.js 14 (App Router) project serving two related brands:
- **refactorsprint.com** - High-velocity strategic sprint service
- **kupermanadvisors.com** - Broader marketing consulting services

Both sites share the same design system but serve different content.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (configured via CSS `@theme` directive in globals.css)
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Fonts**: 
  - Inter (body/UI)
  - JetBrains Mono (data points/technical elements)
- **Deployment**: Vercel
- **Analytics**: HubSpot (Portal ID: 244506871)

## Critical Requirements

### 1. HubSpot Tracking Code (MANDATORY)

**ALL pages must include HubSpot tracking.** This is already implemented in the root layout (`app/layout.tsx`), which applies to all pages automatically.

**If creating a new standalone page or custom layout**, you MUST include:

```tsx
import Script from "next/script";

// Inside the layout/page component, before closing </body>:
<Script
  id="hs-script-loader"
  src="//js-na2.hs-scripts.com/244506871.js"
  strategy="afterInteractive"
/>
```

**HubSpot Code Location**: End of `<body>` tag in `app/layout.tsx`

### 2. HubSpot Contact Form (MANDATORY)

**ALL contact/CTA buttons must link to `/contact`** which contains the HubSpot form.

**Form Details:**
- **Portal ID**: 244506871
- **Form ID**: 3976e6ce-1379-48ca-9b7d-6ba3b45c269e
- **Region**: na2
- **Location**: `/app/contact/page.tsx`

**Contact Button Standard:**
```tsx
<a
  href="/contact"
  className="px-8 py-4 bg-accent-cyan hover:bg-cyan-500 text-slate-900 font-bold rounded-lg transition-all"
>
  Contact / Get Started / Get in Touch
</a>
```

**Never use** `mailto:` links for primary CTAs - always use `/contact` instead.

### 3. Domain Configuration

The project uses Next.js rewrites (configured in `next.config.ts`) to handle multiple domains:

- `refactorsprint.com` → Main site (homepage)
- `refactorsprint.com/ka` → Kuperman Advisors page
- `kupermanadvisors.com` → Automatically shows `/ka` content (via rewrite)

**When creating new pages:**
- Consider which domain(s) should access the page
- Update `next.config.ts` if domain-specific routing is needed

## Design System

### Brand Guidelines

**Complete specifications in `/BRAND_GUIDELINES.md`**

